#. <section class="sutta" id="sn32.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn32.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 32"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 32"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn32.53:0.2"
msgid "1. Valāhakavagga"
msgstr "1. Gods of the Clouds"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 53. Sītavalāhakasutta → sītam (pts1)
msgctxt "sn32.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Sītavalāhakasutta"
msgstr "53. Gods of the Cool Clouds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.256"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn32.53:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn32.53:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated at one side that mendicant said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn32.53:1.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yenekadā sītaṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes it becomes cool?”"

msgctxt "sn32.53:1.4"
msgid "“Santi, bhikkhu, sītavalāhakā nāma devā."
msgstr "“Mendicant, there are what are called gods of the cool clouds."

msgctxt "sn32.53:1.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ yadā evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Sometimes they think:"

#. VAR: ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti → rameyyāmāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn32.53:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘yannūna mayaṃ sakāya ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti, tesaṃ taṃ cetopaṇidhimanvāya "
"sītaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"‘Why don’t we revel in our own kind of enjoyment?’ Then, in accordance with "
"their wish, it becomes cool."

msgctxt "sn32.53:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yenekadā sītaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "This is the cause, this is the reason why sometimes it becomes cool.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn32.53:1.8"
msgid "Tepaññāsamaṃ."
msgstr ""
